tics. However, you can also run the Friedman test using the <strong>Nonpara=
metric Tests &gt; Related Samples</strong> procedure in SPSS Statistics, wh=
ich is available for <strong>versions 18 to 30</strong> and the <strong>sub=
scription version</strong> of SPSS Statistics. This <strong>Nonparametric T=
ests &gt; Related Samples</strong> procedure provides <strong>additional st=
atistics</strong> and <strong>more graphical options</strong> than the <str=
ong>Legacy Dialogs &gt; K Related Samples</strong> procedure. Therefore, we=
 show you how to run the <strong>Nonparametric Tests &gt; Related Samples</=
strong> procedure and interpret and report the output from it in our enhanc=
ed Friedman test guide. You can access the enhanced Friedman test guide by =
